### File Structure
```
CarRental/
│
├── app.py
├── data/
│   ├── vehicles.txt
│   ├── customers.txt
│   ├── locations.txt
│   ├── rentals.txt
│   ├── insurance.txt
│   └── reservations.txt
│
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── vehicle_search.html
│   ├── vehicle_details.html
│   ├── booking.html
│   ├── insurance_options.html
│   ├── rental_history.html
│   ├── reservations.html
│   ├── special_requests.html
│   └── locations.html
│
└── static/
    ├── css/
    │   └── styles.css
    ├── js/
    │   └── scripts.js
    └── images/
        └── (vehicle images and other assets)
```

### File Descriptions
- **app.py**  
  The main backend Python application file. It handles routing, page rendering, reading and writing data from/to the local text files in the `data/` directory, and implements all business logic for the CarRental web application. Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic is consolidated here for simplicity and maintainability.

- **data/**  
  Directory containing all the local text files used for data storage as specified:
  - `vehicles.txt` — Vehicle data.
  - `customers.txt` — Customer data.
  - `locations.txt` — Pickup and dropoff locations data.
  - `rentals.txt` — Rental transactions data.
  - `insurance.txt` — Insurance plans data.
  - `reservations.txt` — Reservation management data.

- **templates/**  
  Contains all HTML template files for the nine pages of the web application, each corresponding to the page designs and element IDs specified in the requirements:
  - `dashboard.html` — Dashboard page.
  - `vehicle_search.html` — Vehicle Search page.
  - `vehicle_details.html` — Vehicle Details page.
  - `booking.html` — Booking page.
  - `insurance_options.html` — Insurance Options page.
  - `rental_history.html` — Rental History page.
  - `reservations.html` — Reservation Management page.
  - `special_requests.html` — Special Requests page.
  - `locations.html` — Locations page.

- **static/**  
  Contains static assets used by the web application:
  - `css/styles.css` — Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
  - `js/scripts.js` — JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., filtering, date pickers).
  - `images/` — Folder for vehicle images and other graphical assets referenced in the UI.

This structure cleanly separates backend logic, data storage, frontend templates, and static resources, facilitating straightforward development, testing, and maintenance of the CarRental web application.
